message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Liberia in the past five years was the 2017 presidential election, which marked the country's first peaceful transfer of power from one democratically elected leader to another in over 70 years. This election saw the victory of George Weah, a former international football star, who became the 25th President of Liberia. Weah's election symbolized a milestone in Liberia's democratic progress and brought hope for political stability and economic development in the country.
